COLLEGENET, INC., Plaintiff-Appellant, v. MARKETLINX, INC., Defendant-Appellee. No. 2012-1083. United States Court of Appeals, Federal Circuit. June 19, 2012. John D. Vandenberg, Klarquist Spark-man, LLP, of Portland, OR, argued for plaintiff-appellant. With him on the brief was Stephen J. Joncus. Floyd R. Nation, Winston & Strawn, LLP, of Houston, TX, argued for the defendant-appellee. With him on the brief was Merritt D. Westcott.

NEWMAN, LOURIE, and PROST, Circuit Judges.

JUDGMENT

PER CURIAM.

This Cause having been heard and considered, it is

Ordered and Adjudged:

AFFIRMED. See Fed. Cir. R. 36.
